        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:39AM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 138 AM MDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Rhame to 5 miles northeast of Mud Buttes to 7
miles west of Table Mountain. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowman, Rhame, Mud Buttes, Griffin, Sunset Butte, and Buffalo
Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Persons in campgrounds should move to a sturdy shelter until these
storms pass.</instruction>
